{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/init(_:)-2758l","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/init(_:)-501qc","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/init(_:)-5hsm6","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/init(_:)-5pcqd","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/init(family:type:protocol:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/init(fd:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/init(opaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/init(raw:)-6zqzn","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/init(raw:)-v02x","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/init(retaining:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/init(retainingCPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/init(retainingOpaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/init(retainingRaw:)-1ord6","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/init(retainingRaw:)-4bbi1","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/init(socket:)"],"generated":true},{"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/metatypeReferenceForSocket","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/wrapperForSocket"],"title":"Instance Properties"},{"generated":true,"title":"Type Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/metatypeForSocket"],"anchor":"Type-Properties"},{"generated":true,"title":"Type Methods","anchor":"Type-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/newFrom(fd:)"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/DatagramBasedProtocol-Implementations","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/InitableProtocol-Implementations","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/SocketProtocol-Implementations"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Default-Implementations","title":"Default Implementations"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Socket","kind":"identifier"}]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocket"},{"type":"text","text":" is the platform independent base upon which the higher level"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"network primitives are based. Applications are not typically meant to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"use it directly, but rather through classes like [class"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketClient","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"],"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[class","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketService","type":"reference"},{"text":"] and [class","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketConnection","isActive":true},{"text":"]. However there may","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"be cases where direct use of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocket"},{"text":" is useful.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocket"},{"type":"text","text":" implements the [iface"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"] interface, so if it is manually","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"constructed by e.g. [ctor"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.Object.new"},{"type":"text","text":"] you must call"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"Gio.Initable.init","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] and check the results before using the object."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This is done automatically in [ctor","type":"text"},{"code":"Gio.Socket.new","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[ctor","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Socket.new_from_fd"},{"type":"text","text":"], so these functions can return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NULL"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Sockets operate in two general modes, blocking or non-blocking. When","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in blocking mode all operations (which don’t take an explicit blocking","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parameter) block until the requested operation"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is finished or there is an error. In non-blocking mode all calls that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"would block return immediately with a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_IO_ERROR_WOULD_BLOCK"},{"type":"text","text":" error."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"To know when a call would successfully run you can call","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Socket.condition_check"},{"text":"], or [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Socket.condition_wait"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"You can also use [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Socket.create_source"},{"type":"text","text":"] and attach it to a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[type[MainContext](\/\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext] to get callbacks when I\/O is possible."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Note that all sockets are always set to non blocking mode in the system, and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"blocking mode is emulated in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocket"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When working in non-blocking mode applications should always be able to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"handle getting a ","type":"text"},{"code":"G_IO_ERROR_WOULD_BLOCK","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" error even when some other","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"function said that I\/O was possible. This can easily happen in case","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of a race condition in the application, but it can also happen for other"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"reasons. For instance, on Windows a socket is always seen as writable"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"until a write returns ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_IO_ERROR_WOULD_BLOCK"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocket"},{"text":"s can be either connection oriented or datagram based.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"For connection oriented types you must first establish a connection by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"either connecting to an address or accepting a connection from another","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"address. For connectionless socket types the target\/source address is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"specified or received in each I\/O operation."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All socket file descriptors are set to be close-on-exec."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that creating a "},{"code":"GSocket","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" causes the signal "},{"code":"SIGPIPE","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ignored for the remainder of the program. If you are writing a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"command-line utility that uses ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocket"},{"type":"text","text":", you may need to take into"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"account the fact that your program will not automatically be killed","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"if it tries to write to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stdout"},{"type":"text","text":" after it has been closed."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Like most other APIs in GLib, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocket"},{"text":" is not inherently thread safe. To use","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"a ","type":"text"},{"code":"GSocket","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" concurrently from multiple threads, you must implement your own","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"locking."}]},{"text":"Nagle’s algorithm","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Nagles-algorithm"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Since GLib 2.80, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocket"},{"text":" will automatically set the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TCP_NODELAY"},{"type":"text","text":" option on"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"all "},{"code":"G_SOCKET_TYPE_STREAM","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" sockets. This disables"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nagle%27s_algorithm","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" as it"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"typically does more harm than good on modern networks.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your application needs Nagle’s algorithm enabled, call"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"Gio.Socket.set_option","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] after constructing a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocket"},{"type":"text","text":" to enable it:"}]},{"syntax":"c","code":["socket = g_socket_new (…, G_SOCKET_TYPE_STREAM, …);","if (socket != NULL)","  {","    g_socket_set_option (socket, IPPROTO_TCP, TCP_NODELAY, FALSE, &local_error);","    \/\/ handle error if needed","  }"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a reference-counted owner of an underlying "},{"code":"GSocket","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" as a strong reference or owner of a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocket"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketRef","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocket"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocket"},{"text":" is a low-level networking primitive. It is a more or less","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"direct mapping of the BSD socket API in a portable GObject based API.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It supports both the UNIX socket implementations and winsock2 on Windows.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/socket"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"inheritsFrom","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/10GLibObject0B0C"],"title":"Inherits From"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DatagramBasedProtocol","doc:\/\/GIO\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/GIO\/10GLibObject0B8ProtocolP","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InitableProtocol","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketProtocol"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Socket","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Class","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Socket","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"class","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"externalID":"s:3GIO6SocketC","title":"Socket"},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Socket/init(retaining:)":{"type":"topic","role":"symbol","title":"init(retaining:)","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socket\/init(retaining:)","fragments":[{"text":"init","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"retaining","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"GSocket","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">)","kind":"text"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Designated initialiser from the underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"C"},{"text":" data type.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Will retain "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocket"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"i.e., ownership is transferred to t